The President met with CEOs from various sectors to discuss improving cybersecurity of critical infrastructure. They discussed the voluntary Cybersecurity Framework, which lays out core practices for organizations to manage cybersecurity risk. The CEOs expressed support for the framework and discussed the need for its adoption by both critical infrastructure and suppliers. They also expressed the desire for Congress to pass information sharing legislation that protects privacy and civil liberties. Attendees included CEOs from MasterCard, Symantec, Northrup Grumman, Lockheed Martin, Intel, Bank of America, Pepco Holdings, and Visa.